pullRequest.body:
All of these declarations have been deprecated since their files were ported (in January 2023).

Move `nthLe` from `Init` to `List/Basic`, next to the other lemmas using it.

---

Now rebased on #9607.
- [x] depends on: #12362 (preliminary clean-up; discovered in fixing the build here)
- [x] depends on: #12367 (some easy changes)
- [x] depends on: #12397 
- [x] depends on: #12398

**[lint-style]** reported by [reviewdog](https://github.com/reviewdog/reviewdog) :dog:
```suggestion â† nthLe_permutations'Aux t x s.length (by simp [hl])] ```

I *want* to, but cannot: the `@deprecated` attribute accepts *either* a replacement declaration or a date. I decided the replacement was more useful, especially since `nthLe` is still used in a number of places.
Oh huh. Can you file an issue for that?

... turns out I was wrong :tada: the date has to come *after* the new name, though.
When going over mathlib and reformatting dates to use this syntax, this place and and should be updated as well.
